<h2 id=3D"id-2025/08/04-EnhancingUserControlforSREAgentWorkflows-Context/Pr=
oblemStatement">Context / Problem Statement</h2>
<p>Our SRE agent needs to be able to <a href=3D"https://newrelic.atlassian.=
net/wiki/x/2AI9DQE" rel=3D"nofollow">perform various automated workflows</a=
> in order to align to the limited preview requirements. In order to accomp=
lish this we have a few tools and configurations for workflows.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>We have <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://source.datanerd.us/Al=
erting/sre-agent/blob/master/mcp-server/src/sre_agent/agents/remediation_ag=
ent/workflow_automation.py#L68" rel=3D"nofollow">a tool</a> that will searc=
h for automated workflows that have a specified tag <code>nerdEnabled</code=
> set to <code>true</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>We have <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://source.datanerd.us/Al=
erting/sre-agent/blob/master/mcp-server/src/sre_agent/agents/remediation_ag=
ent/workflow_automation.py#L17" rel=3D"nofollow">a tool</a> to perform a sp=
ecified automated workflow by name</p></li>
<li>
<p>There are other tools such as a GitHub issue creation tool which should =
be transient as ongoing work is performed by the workflow automation and wo=
rk item teams</p></li>
</ul>
<p>The agent=E2=80=99s instructions include the need to<span class=3D"inlin=
e-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"b258f8a5-8ba4-4470-82bc-a8b2290be8ea"> </span=
><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://source.datanerd.us/Alerting/sre=
-agent/blob/master/agent-configs/agents/sre-agent%3Av0.0.1/agents/mitigatin=
g_actions_agent%3Av0.0.1_prompt.txt#L60" rel=3D"nofollow"><span class=3D"in=
line-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"b258f8a5-8ba4-4470-82bc-a8b2290be8ea">ask =
for confirmation before running a workflow</span></a><span class=3D"inline-=
comment-marker" data-ref=3D"b258f8a5-8ba4-4470-82bc-a8b2290be8ea">.</span> =
As the context window/conversation grows we will see<span class=3D"inline-c=
omment-marker" data-ref=3D"8d0af0b8-9fd8-4023-a879-45d9e1ce678a"> older tok=
ens truncated</span>. As the agent's responsibility and default context gro=
ws we can predict this truncation will be more readily reached during the e=
xecution of the SRE agent. Instructions will get lost and the agent will mo=
re readily do what it wants regardless of our <code>ask nicely for permissi=
ons</code> instructions. Bugs such as hallucinations and forgetting instruc=
tions are a well known flaw in these features and in this scenario this cou=
ld readily cause another case of <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:/=
/www.businessinsider.com/replit-ceo-apologizes-ai-coding-tool-delete-compan=
y-database-2025-7" rel=3D"nofollow">Replit's rogue deletion of all things</=
a>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-2025/08/04-EnhancingUserControlforSREAgentWorkflows-Design">De=
sign</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Generate a Confirmation Request:</strong> Instead of directly pe=
rforming a mitigation, the agent generates a <strong>confirmation request</=
strong> that contains all the instructions for the proposed action.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"8399f5f2-9886-4bd7-ad4=
e-1aba42f9fa70">Need: Store this confirmation request. Example data sources=
 might be:</span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Work item</p></li>
<li>
<p>A new database</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>User Review and Approval:</strong> The request is presented to t=
he user for review. The user must explicitly approve the request before any=
 action is taken.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Need: UX work for the Collaboration team as well as to any other integra=
tion points</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Trigger Automation:</strong> Once the user approves the request,=
 the automation is triggered.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Need: Execution of confirmation request</p></li>
<li>
<p>Need: Continuation of SRE agent thread</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>This model is similar to how GitHub Copilot suggests an action rather th=
an executing it directly. This change gives users explicit control and ensu=
res consent before an action is performed, reducing risk.</p><span class=3D=
"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-=
manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"i=
mage-20250804-165225.png" width=3D"462" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"4ef7cb5c290=
97add3b848fd362df650d82e9b270b2b016ac10ed91912dc9be3c" data-image-src=3D"ht=
tps://newrelic.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/4533026951/image-202=
50804-165225.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1754326350531&amp;cache=
Version=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"241" data-width=3D"462" data-unres=
olved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"4533059617" data-linke=
d-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-link=
ed-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20250804-165225.png" data-base-url=3D"ht=
tps://newrelic.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"ima=
ge/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"4533026951" data-linked-resour=
ce-container-version=3D"2" data-media-id=3D"20171d48-ae17-46d2-9311-19b6ba4=
14d3f" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"241"></span>
<h4 id=3D"id-2025/08/04-EnhancingUserControlforSREAgentWorkflows-Pros">Pros=
</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Mature user consent flow</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"id-2025/08/04-EnhancingUserControlforSREAgentWorkflows-Cons">Cons=
</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Notable scope change for supporting the new workflow consent flow</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p></p>
    </div>
</body>
